genresAdvancedInfo.name: pibroch
genresAdvancedInfo.description: Pibroch is a traditional Scottish music genre that is played on the bagpipes. The music is characterized by its complex and intricate melodies, which are often based on ancient Gaelic tunes. Pibroch is typically performed at formal events such as weddings and funerals, and it is deeply rooted in Scottish culture and tradition.
